President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the State of Alabama, allowing federal aid to supplement state and local response efforts after severe storms, tornadoes, and straight-line winds struck the area on April 27, 2011. The Department of Homeland Security, through FEMA, will coordinate all disaster relief efforts to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources as needed to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be at 75 percent. Joe M. Girot has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.